headline: CEO of $30 billion homebuilding empire sees ‘weaker-for-longer’ housing market as consumer confidence plummets
summary: “Mortgage interest rates have remained higher-for-longer, which has left the overall housing market weaker-for-longer,” Lennar chairman and co-CEO Stuart Miller said in an earnings call.
